<span id="freeTextContainer16853139298471639571">If you like Gabriel Garcia Marquez or Isabel Allende, you must read this beautiful story about the unrequited love Hadriel has for Sophia Paula ever since the age of twelve. They become friends, best friends; Hadriel falls for her, yet she goes away the moment he pronounces love and he loves her for a lifetime.<br/><br/>From the delightful setting of Santa Lucia, in South America, to El Norte, Chicago, in the States, Hadriel carries his broken heart, yet fulfils other dreams.<br/><br/>Felix Alexander is a great sto</span>
  <span id="freeText16853139298471639571" style="display:none">If you like Gabriel Garcia Marquez or Isabel Allende, you must read this beautiful story about the unrequited love Hadriel has for Sophia Paula ever since the age of twelve. They become friends, best friends; Hadriel falls for her, yet she goes away the moment he pronounces love and he loves her for a lifetime.<br /><br />From the delightful setting of Santa Lucia, in South America, to El Norte, Chicago, in the States, Hadriel carries his broken heart, yet fulfils other dreams.<br /><br />Felix Alexander is a great story-teller, his writing evocative and delicate, yet sparse, but full of feelings and beautiful descriptions, just to the point and very skilful. This is objective writing which conjures many deep sensations, beyond the words.<br /><br />Thoroughly enjoyable and recommended... </span>
