<div id="review_1617633192" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1617633192" />
    <a title="Ariana Fae" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/29984848-ariana-fae"><img alt="Ariana Fae" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1451784114p2/29984848.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1617633192?book_show_action=true">Apr 22, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ariana Fae" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ariana Fae" href="/user/show/29984848-ariana-fae">Ariana Fae</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1617633192" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5102195840363301636">The Romantic by Felix Alexander is a departure from the usual genre I love to read in. I was pleasantly surprised by this memorizing story about love. You can tell the author is true poet at heart by his prose, use of imagery and how he writes about love and the human heart. <br/><br/>Hadriel, the protagonist, is a man cursed to love women who can’t reciprocate his amour is an interesting character. Through his eyes, and the women he loves, we see love in all its facets, the sacrifices, stupidities and sh</span>
  <span id="freeText5102195840363301636" style="display:none">The Romantic by Felix Alexander is a departure from the usual genre I love to read in. I was pleasantly surprised by this memorizing story about love. You can tell the author is true poet at heart by his prose, use of imagery and how he writes about love and the human heart. <br /><br />Hadriel, the protagonist, is a man cursed to love women who can’t reciprocate his amour is an interesting character. Through his eyes, and the women he loves, we see love in all its facets, the sacrifices, stupidities and shames we commit for it.<br /><br />I will admit it took me a few chapters to get into the book, which could because it was a new genre for me, but then I was drawn into Hadriel’s journey. I wanted to know who he would find true love with. And the ending was not what I expected and made my eyes mist up.<br /><br />The Romantic is a tale that speaks about love and the intricate dance it weaves in and out of our lives. I’m looking forward to reading more of Felix Alexander’s works. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5102195840363301636" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
